The table below identifies possible bitcoin scammers who've used this site. If your account details appear on this list, and you're not a scammer, please contact us immediately to resolve this situation.

To avoid bitcoin scams we always recommend using a bitcoin escrow service. Bitcoin buyers should insist that bitcoins are in escrow before any payment is made.

Identifying potential scammers

In general the following points should be used as a guide to identify potential scammers:

  • Is their bitcoin sell price too low? Or buy price too high?
  • Do they refuse to use escrow?
  • How long have they been a member (in their profile page)?
  • Do they have excessive feedback shortly after joining?
  • Do they only have automated feedback?

What can I do if I've been scammed

If you've been scammed by someone selling bitcoins to you you can try to have charges reversed. You may have success with PayPal, Moneybookers, or other credit card based payment services. You can also leave negative feedback which will help others to avoid that scammer. Unfortunately there's not much more we can recommend you do.

What happens when I report a scammer

We immediately ban their account and all their current orders. If it's a serious breach, and we beleive they use a static IP address we will also ban their IP address. We may also ban a range of IP addresses as needed.
